      "name": "Normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) validation against in-vitro loop experiments",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis compared against in-vitro hemolysis loop experiments at five operating points. Relative hemolysis index RH computed for each point; all five points satisfy RH < 1 acceptance criterion relative to predicate device. Inherent variability in biological assay measurements (sample-to-sample variation in red blood cell fragility, lot-to-lot variation in blood analog) assessed qualitatively by subject matter experts and noted in the study report. No structured UQ node is linked to this validation result; aleatory uncertainty from biological variability remains uncharacterized in machine-readable form."
    },
